OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784816319
OL,3,CFood prices are helping keep inflation
OL,4,Cin check - but will the good news last?
OL,6,FThe annual rate of inflation in the UK
OL,7,Feased to 2.6% last month - above the
OL,8,FBank of England's 2% target but well
OL,9,Fbelow almost everyone's expectations.
OL,11,FThe Bank had pencilled in 3%, to
OL,12,Freflect the surge in oil and gas
OL,13,Fprices after the outbreak of the
OL,14,Fconflict in the Gulf.
OL,16,FBack in April, the International
OL,17,FMonetary Fund expected the UK to be on
OL,18,Fa slow march towards 4% by the end of
OL,19,Fthe year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784816319
OL,3,CFood prices are helping keep inflation
OL,4,Cin check - but will the good news last?
OL,6,FSo what has gone right? Prices have
OL,7,Fcontinued to rise but not on the scale
OL,8,Fmany economists feared.
OL,10,FLast month, the cost of hotels and
OL,11,Fairfares - which are often volatile at
OL,12,Fthis time of year - were relatively
OL,13,Fstable.
OL,15,FRetailers also appear, for now at
OL,16,Fleast, to have absorbed much of the
OL,17,Fincrease in their own costs rather
OL,18,Fthan passing them on to consumers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
