PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784816319
OL,3,CFood prices are helping keep inflation
OL,4,Cin check - but will the good news last?
OL,6,FMeasures such as the temporary removal
OL,7,Fof VAT on domestic electricity and a
OL,8,F#2 cap on bus fares are relatively
OL,9,Finexpensive for the Treasury,
OL,10,Fpolitically popular, and together
OL,11,Fcould shave around 0.1 percentage
OL,12,Fpoints off the headline rate of
OL,13,Finflation.
OL,15,FFew economists, however, believe the
OL,16,Fgood news will last.
OL,18,FOfgem's energy price cap rose by 13%
OL,19,Fthis month and that increase will feed
OL,20,Finto next month's inflation figures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
